@page "/introduction/general-rules-and-guidelines"

@inherits GeneralRulesAndGuidelinesBase

<DocsPage MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large">
    <DocsPageHeader Title="General Rules and Guidelines for ATC-Net organisation">
    </DocsPageHeader>
    <DocsPageContent>

        <DocsPageSection>
            <SectionHeader Title="Introduction"/>
            <SectionContent>
                <p>
                    The ATC-Net organization repositories are split up and managed by people from the core team, referred to as ATC-team.
                </p>

                <ul style="list-style-type: square">
                    <li>All repositories are free to use and contribute to - ATC-Net uses the <b>MIT license</b>.</li>
                    <li>Everyone can contribute to a repository by making a pull-request (PR).</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    The process for creating a new repository, must go through the ATC-team.

                    This process involves a few steps

                    <ul style="list-style-type: square">
                        <li>Giving the repository a meaningful name</li>
                        <li>Defining the purpose of the repository through a good description</li>
                        <li>Follow the general ATC repository template</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    When creating a repository on the atc-net organization, the above mentioned rules must be followed.
                    If in need to create a "startup" repository, the <MudLink Href="https://github.com/sandbox-atc-net">Sandbox ATC-NET Organization</MudLink> can be used.
                </p>
            </SectionContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

    </DocsPageContent>
</DocsPage>